observations.recommendation:
We recommended that management:
Should strictly comply with the pertinent provisions of P.D. 1445 and COA Circular No. 97-002 on the grant, utilization, and liquidations of cash advances and enforce all possible means to settle cash advances;
Issue demand letters to active officials and employees and send final demand letter to persons who have retired or out of service who still have unliquidated cash advances;
Deduct from the claims of officers and employees retiring from the service the amount of their unliquidated cash advances and clearance of retiring/ transferring officers/ employees should not be given or released unless settlement of outstanding cash advances have been made;
File request for write off of dormant receivables account as per COA Circular 2016-005; and
Effect the necessary adjustment for discrepancies between financial statement and subsidiary ledger under general fund and locate available documents to prepare subsidiary ledger for trust fund account.

We recommended that management:

Issue demand letters to: (1) concerned officials and employees to settle their unliquidated cash advances. If no settlement was received, withhold their salaries considering that they have been notified and given adequate time to liquidate; (2) employees who either resigned or retired to immediately cause the liquidation or settlement of their unliquidated advances;

Request the write-off of unliquidated cash advance balances of the deceased employees;

Secure consent and deduct from the claims of officers and employees retiring from the service the amount of their unliquidated cash advances. Clearances of retiring/transferring officers/employees should not be given or released unless settlement of outstanding cash advances have been made;

Grant cash advance to officers and employees for their travelling expenses only except for those designated special disbursing officers who may be granted special cash advances for other legally authorized purposes; and

Strictly comply with the pertinent provisions of P.D. 1445 and COA Circular 97-002 on the grant, utilization, and liquidations of cash advances and exhaust all possible means to settle cash advances.

We reiterated our recommendation and the Municipal Accountant-ICO and  Municipal Treasurer agreed  to:

Scrutinize the details of the non-moving cash advances especially the balances as of December 31, 2015 and require the concerned officials and employees to settle immediately their respective outstanding cash advances, otherwise, make use of available legal remedies as summarized under Section 9.0 of COA Circular No. 2012-004 dated November 28, 2012; 

Comply strictly with guidelines on the grant, utilization and liquidation of cash advances provided in COA Circular No. 97-002 as reiterated in COA Circular No. 2012-004 and; 

Monitor compliance thereof to prevent the accumulation of cash advances;

Issue final demand letters and the proper officials to initiate appropriate sanctions to  officers and employees who will not settle their accounts;
Issue certification that the previous cash advances has been liquidated and accounted for in the books before another cash advance be granted.  No cash advance shall be granted without the required certification, otherwise official/s who allowed the grant of the cash advance should be held liable thereof.
